eu.slipo.athenarc.triplegeo.tools

Class OsmXmlToRdf

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
      • eu.slipo.athenarc.triplegeo.tools.OsmXmlToRdf
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.xml.sax.ContentHandler, org.xml.sax.DTDHandler, org.xml.sax.EntityResolver, org.xml.sax.ErrorHandler

    public class OsmXmlToRdf
extends org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
    Entry point to convert OpenStreetMap (OSM) XML files into RDF triples using Saxon XSLT. LIMITATIONS: - Depending on system and JVM resources, transformation can handle only a moderate amount of OSM features. - RML transformation mode not currently supported.
    Version:
    1.8
    Author:
    Kostas Patroumpas

      • OsmXmlToRdf

        public OsmXmlToRdf(Configuration config,
                   java.lang.String inFile,
                   java.lang.String outFile,
                   int sourceSRID,
                   int targetSRID)
        Constructor for the transformation process from OpenStreetMap XML file to RDF.
        Parameters:
        config - Parameters to configure the transformation.
        inFile - Path to input OSM XML file.
        outFile - Path to the output file that collects RDF triples.
        sourceSRID - Spatial reference system (EPSG code) of the input OSM XML file.
        targetSRID - Spatial reference system (EPSG code) of geometries in the output RDF triples.
